  "metadata": {
    "title": "RLIMIT_STACK/RLIMIT_INFINITY string size limitation bypass (low)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2017-1000365",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2017-1000365",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: The Linux Kernel imposes a size restriction on the arguments and environmental strings passed through RLIMIT_STACK/RLIMIT_INFINITY, but does not take the argument and environment pointers into account, which allows attackers to bypass this limitation. \n            STATEMENT: This issue affects the Linux kernel packages as shipped with Red Hat\nEnterprise Linux 5,6, 7 and MRG-2.\n\nFuture Linux kernel updates for the respective releases may address this issue.",
